The body of a man who drowned in a dam in Durban on Saturday has been recovered, KwaZulu-Natal police said. Earlier today [Saturday] police divers from Durban search and rescue along with IPSS Medical Rescue, Pietermaritzburg K9 search and rescue, and Captain Wessels (DivComm water policing HQ) responded to a drowning incident in the Ngcolosi area in Hillcrest at the Inanda Dam, police said in a statement on the official South African Police Service (SAPS) Facebook page. A 33-year-old man was washing clothing in the dam. It s understood the man swam into the dam to cool down when he got into difficulty and drowned. The victim was recovered from a depth of four metres by the divers after K9 [sniffer dog] Chaz identified the location. An inquest docket has been opened. 